<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1951,2014]" lastBlockId="34.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1951,1977]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</emphasis>
The diagnostic features of 
<emphasis box="[560,853,1951,1980]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2021" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2021" box="[560,702,1951,1977]" genus="Bathyccpcla" pageId="31" pageNumber="41" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Bathycçpçla</taxonomicName>
brevẚcaudata
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,1025,1951,1977]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">gen. et sp. nov.</emphasis>
are; (1) the dorsal tergite of the fourth pedigerous somite extends posteriorly to cover most of the urosome; (2) the maxillary endopod is 1-segmented and armed with five setae; (3) the second exopodal segments of legs 2-4 are each armed with 7 spines and 1 seta; (4) the second endopodal segments of legs 2-4 are each armed with 4 spines and 1 seta; and (5) the inner coxal seta present only in leg 4. These diagnostic features serve to distinguish the new species from its congeners.
</paragraph>
